// ============================================================
// inject_rtti_err_denylist_destroy.lox — Denylist blocks Destroy()
// ============================================================
// Setup: Delphi injects a TCustomer as global 'cust'.
//
// What this tests:
//   - Attempting to call Destroy() on an injected object from Lox
//   - The RTTI method denylist should block this with a runtime error
//   - Prevents scripts from calling the destructor on host-owned objects
print cust.Name; // expect: Alice
cust.Destroy(); // expect runtime error: Method 'Destroy' is not callable from script.
